# .cursorule for Viral Together UI (Next.js 14)

# Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 UI application for the Viral Together influencer marketing platform.
It connects to the API repository at ../viral-together and provides a modern web interface.

# Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- React Hook Form
- Axios for API calls
- Lucide React for icons

# Development Commands
dev: npm run dev
build: npm run build
start: npm run start
lint: npm run lint
type-check: npm run type-check

# Environment Variables
API_URL: http://localhost:8000 (points to the viral-together API)
NODE_ENV: development

# Key Directories
- src/app: Next.js 14 App Router pages
- src/components: Reusable React components
- src/lib: Utility functions and API client
- src/types: TypeScript type definitions
- src/hooks: Custom React hooks

# API Integration
The app integrates with the viral-together API for:
- Authentication (JWT tokens)
- Influencer management
- Rate card management
- Subscription handling
- Search and analytics

# Specify the test command for running tests
test: npm run test

# Design System & Theme Guidelines
# The following design system MUST be maintained throughout UI development:

## Color Schema
Primary Colors (Blue Gradient):
  - primary-50: #f0f9ff (lightest blue)
  - primary-500: #0ea5e9 (main blue)
  - primary-600: #0284c7 (primary brand color)
  - primary-700: #0369a1 (hover states)

Secondary Colors (Purple Gradient):
  - secondary-500: #d946ef (accent purple)
  - secondary-600: #c026d3 (secondary brand color)

Neutral Colors:
  - gray-50: #f9fafb (backgrounds)
  - gray-100: #f3f4f6 (subtle backgrounds)
  - gray-200: #e5e7eb (borders)
  - gray-300: #d1d5db (borders/dividers)
  - gray-600: #4b5563 (secondary text)
  - gray-900: #111827 (primary text)
  - white: #ffffff (cards/surfaces)

## Typography
Font Family: Inter (Google Fonts)
- Primary font for all text content
- Weights: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700
- System fallback: system-ui, sans-serif

## Component Patterns
Button Variants:
  - .btn-primary: primary-600 background, white text
  - .btn-secondary: gray-200 background, gray-900 text
  - .btn-outline: transparent with gray-300 border
  - .btn-ghost: transparent with hover gray-100

Button Sizes:
  - .btn-sm: h-9 px-3 (small)
  - .btn-md: h-10 px-4 py-2 (default)
  - .btn-lg: h-11 px-8 (large)

Form Elements:
  - .input: Standard input styling with primary-500 focus ring
  - Border: gray-300, Focus: primary-500 ring

Cards:
  - .card: rounded-lg border bg-white p-6 shadow-sm
  - Consistent 6-unit padding, subtle shadow

## Gradient System
Signature Gradient:
  - .gradient-bg: bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 via-primary-600 to-secondary-600
  - Used for: Hero sections, CTAs, feature icons, brand elements

## Layout Patterns
Container: container mx-auto px-4 (responsive container)
Spacing: Consistent use of Tailwind spacing scale (4, 6, 8, 12, 16, 20)
Grid: CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts
Responsive: Mobile-first approach with md: and lg: breakpoints

## Animation Standards
Transitions: transition-colors for interactive elements
Custom Animations:
  - fade-in: 0.5s ease-in-out
  - slide-up: 0.3s ease-out
Loading States: Spin animation for loading indicators

## Icon System
Library: Lucide React
Style: Consistent sizing (w-4 h-4, w-5 h-5, w-6 h-6)
Usage: Semantic icons for navigation, actions, and features

## Accessibility Standards
Focus States: focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary-500
Color Contrast: WCAG AA compliant color combinations
Interactive Elements: Proper hover and disabled states

## Development Rules
- ALWAYS use the cn() utility for className merging
- MAINTAIN consistent spacing using Tailwind scale
- USE semantic color names (primary, secondary, gray)
- FOLLOW component composition patterns
- ENSURE responsive design with mobile-first approach
- PRESERVE gradient branding throughout the application

